// ============================================================================
// Lint waivers (verilator_config below) for BSC (Bluespec) library Verilog
// pulled into {{ip_name}}'s verilog/ output dir.
//
// NOTE: don't start any comment line in this file with the bare word
// "verilator" (case-insensitive) — Verilator treats that as a pragma-
// comment attempt and errors with BADVLTPRAGMA if what follows isn't a
// recognized pragma keyword (lint_off, public, tracing_off, ...). This bit
// us once already; keep "verilator" away from the first-word position.
//
// bsv/Makefile's copy_files target copies BSC's own FIFO*.v/SizedFIFO.v/
// BRAM*.v primitive models from $(BLUESPEC_HOME)/lib/Verilog directly into
// this IP's verilog/ output dir (LibreLane needs a self-contained source
// dir), so they can't be scoped out by directory — match by filename
// instead. This keeps the sim-code-leak detector in verilator.flags
// (INITIALDLY/STMTDLY kept fatal) fully intact for {{ip_name}}'s own
// generated RTL (mk{{ip_name|capitalize}}.v, mkConfigCSR_*.v, etc.) — these
// vendor primitives are outside our control, not signals of a real problem.
//
// Author: {{author}} <{{email}}>
// ============================================================================
`verilator_config

lint_off -rule INITIALDLY -file "*/FIFO*.v"
lint_off -rule STMTDLY    -file "*/FIFO*.v"
lint_off -rule INITIALDLY -file "*/SizedFIFO.v"
lint_off -rule STMTDLY    -file "*/SizedFIFO.v"
lint_off -rule INITIALDLY -file "*/BRAM*.v"
lint_off -rule STMTDLY    -file "*/BRAM*.v"
